      <link>https://www.filippobroggini.com/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Feb 2020 01:09:59 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.filippobroggini.com/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Summary&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;👋 I am Filippo. I am a senior solutions engineer (and jack of all trades) at &lt;a href=&#34;https://squirro.com/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Squirro&lt;/a&gt;. Previously, I was a researcher in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://eeg.ethz.ch/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Exploration and Environmental Geophysics group&lt;/a&gt; at ETH Zürich. I have 10 years of experience in computational and theoretical Geophysics. I am passionate about data science, education, and teaching. I co-supervised PhD students and MSc students, and taught a BSc class on geophysical methods. In my spare time (what is left after spending time with my lovely family), I read, cook, build a Raspberry Pi cluster, do sports, and update my personal website.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
